02/02/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic met with Macedonian counterpart Branko Crvenkovski on Tuesday (1 February), focusing on the demarcation of the border between their countries and on the fight against organised crime. 
Crvenkovski stressed that border demarcation must be resolved as soon as possible and must involve input from residents of the border regions. 
Crvenkovski and Serbian President Boris Tadic discussed a possible joint initiative for a regional summit on combating organised crime and corruption. 
They also talked about the situation in Kosovo, but no details were disclosed. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik, Danas - 02/02/05; Tanjug, A1 TV - 01/02/05)
